title: Bearded Eagle looms Carlton’s biggest blue
text:
AFL Grand Final: West Coast and Carlton traded Chris Judd for Josh Kennedy - who won? Andrew Hamilton News Limited AFL Grand Final: West Coast and Carlton traded Chris Judd for Josh Kennedy - who won? Andrew Hamilton News Limited Jeremy McGovern feeling good 0:55 
AFL: West Coast defender Jeremy McGovern says he is feeling good ahead of the Premiership decider against Hawthorn this weekend October 1st 2015 a day ago /video/video.news.com.au/Sport/AFL/News/ 
CHRIS Judd will join the motorcade of retiring greats around the MCG tomorrow before Josh Kennedy kickstarts his engine and gets to work with the Eagles’ hopes of flag glory resting on his broad shoulders. 
The pair were the key figures in the biggest trade of the modern era back in 2007. 
West Coast gave Carlton Judd and pick 46 for Kennedy and picks three and 20. 
They used pick three for Chris Masten who is a key midfield member tomorrow while Tony Notte (20) was a bust. 
The Blues got the best player in the game and used their extra pick to recruit loyal servant Dennis Armfield. 
So, who won — West Coast or Carlton? Other Stories
